### Gallery

These example images have been generated using pepper's built-in
reports.  The corresponding command-line arguments for pepper are
listed below the thumbnails.  In order to achieve similar output
in quality and color, you should use the `pngcairo` terminal and
place [this .gnuplot file](.gnuplot) in your home directory. The
Gnuplot style has been mostly copied from [this GuidoLabs
article](http://guidolan.blogspot.com/2010/03/how-to-create-beautiful-gnuplot-graphs.html).

Several large repositories of free and open-source software have been
used for generating the reports below (the links to the repositories
can be found in the respective captions). Please click on an image
to access its full-resolution version.

